This tool will return an object that contains fields for the creation of a bar chart. 
The object contains the following fields: `x_values`, `y_values`, `caption`, `x_label`, and `y_label`. 
The `x_values` field is an array of numerical or categorical values representing the data points along the X-axis. 
The `y_values` field is an array of numbers representing the corresponding data points along the Y-axis. 
The `caption` field is a string that provides a brief description or title for the bar chart. 
The `x_label` and `y_label` fields are strings representing the labels for the X-axis and Y-axis, respectively.
Each value in the `x_values` array corresponds to the value at the same index in the `y_values` array.

